{"id": 6220, "title": "Ticket #6220: Turn off submit file checks by default", "description": "<blockquote>\nBy default, at submit time, the schedd checks to see if the job's stdin, stdout, and stderr files are readable and writeable, respectively.  However, this puts additional load on the schedd, results in confusing error messages if some system puts them in the right state before job exit, and doesn't work today in the AFS case.  Let's just turn this off by default.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2017-Jun-19 13:16:04 by tim:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>DOC REVIEW:</strong> Admin section needs to be updated. Appear to have 2 version history commits.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2017-Jun-20 15:27</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/223d66d2af271d23d905b27fb59438b7965a5c61\">[51773]</a></span>: Fixed lies in version history blurb. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=6220\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6220'); return false;\" title=\"Turn off submit file checks by default\">#6220</a></span>  (By Todd Tannenbaum )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2017-Jun-20 11:12</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/0a3520559c2dd279c96ce9efbcfbaabef1963652\">[51750]</a></span>: Update admin-man for <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=6220\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrappe